<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN372">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>vicipiṇit taṭāri vimmeṉa voṟṟi</l>
<l>yētti vanta tellā muḻutta</l>
<l>vilaṅkuvā ḷaviroḷi valampaṭa miṉṉik</l>
<l>kaṇaittuḷi poḻinta kaṇkūṭu pācaṟaip</l>
<l>poruntāt tevva rarintatalai yaṭuppiṟ</l>
<l>kūviḷa viṟaki ṉākkuvari nuṭaṅka</l>
<l>lāṉā maṇṭai vaṉṉiyan tuṭuppi</l>
<l>ṉīṉā vēṇmā ḷiṭantuḻan taṭṭa</l>
<l>māmaṟi piṇṭam vāluva ṉēnta</l>
<l>vatuvai viḻaviṟ putuvōrk kellām</l>
<l>vevvāyp peyta pūtanīr cālkeṉap</l>
<l>pulavukkaḷam poliya vēṭṭōyniṉ</l>
<l>ṉilavuttika ḻāra mukakkuva meṉavē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Loudly beating the Taṭāri drum tied with straps (1)</l>
<l>[we] came, praising [you], (2ab)</l>
<l>in the war camp that joins the area where arrows had flown as [rain] drops, (4)</l>
<l>with the shining light of shining swords flashing victorioulsly, (3)</l>
<l>	all at once(?), (2cd)</l>
<l>thinking that we will draw pearl-strings glimmering of moonlight, (13)</l>
<l>from you who sacrificed so that the flesh-reeking battle field flourishes, (12)</l>
<l>saying “let you Bhūtas be many into whose red mouths is poured (11)</l>
<l>all [given to] newcomers at wedding feasts, (10)</l>
<l>when the cook offers balls of dark kid (9)</l>
<l>that was cooked, stirring the place, by a Vēṇmāḷ woman who had not given birth, (8)</l>
<l>with a Vaṉṉi-wooden ladle into unending bowls, (7)</l>
<l>on the fireplace [made] of the cut-off heads of uncouth enemies (5)</l>
<l>kindling(?) firewood of Bael, swaying in lines. (6) </l>
</lg>
    </div>
